{
  "texts": [
    "In this respect, correspondence theory for possibility semantics is similar to intuitionistic correspondence theory, as developed in Rodenburg 1986, which shares the persistence constraint on valuations.Thus, we need methods of constructing admissible valuations on full possibility frames.",
    "From Fact 4.3, we know that if for each p ∈ Φ, we set π(p) = {x ′ ∈ S | x ′ ⊑ s x} for some x ∈ S, then π is admissible.",
    "More generally, from Fact 2.17.2, we know that if for each p ∈ Φ we setπ(p) = int(cl(⇓X)) = {x ∈ S | ∀x ′ ⊑ x ∃x ′′ ⊑ x ′: x ′′ ∈ ⇓X}for some X ⊆ S, then π is admissible.",
    "The following gives another way of ensuring that π is admissible.",
    "Since x ′ ⊑ x and x ⊥ y together imply x ′ ⊥ y, {x ∈ S | ∀y ∈ Y, x ⊥ y} satisfies persistence.For refinability, suppose x ̸ ∈ {x ∈ S | ∀y ∈ Y, x ⊥ y}, so there is a y ∈ Y such that x ≬ y."
  ]
}